Description: Up for sale is a 1996 Jackson PS4, Made in Japan, Performer Series guitar, with a upgraded Seymour Duncan Screamin demon TB-12 bridge pickup, and this guitar comes with a Epiphone gig bag.(serial number is 9614526) This is a nice Jackson super strat style guitar, and the neck is a little on the wider side. If you like the feel of wider, and flatter radius necks, you'll probably like this neck. Personally, I find them much more comfortable to play. The Screamin Demon pickup was developed in conjunction with George Lynch from Dokken, but the name can be a little misleading... It is not a super high output pickup. If you are playing through an amp with plenty of overdrive to spare, you'll probably like this pickup. But if you have an amp that has a hard time breaking up, and you need a high output pickup to drive it for it into distortion, this pickup may not be hot enough for you, if you like heavy overdrive. To the winning bidder:This guitar will be well boxed and fully insured, to help make sure it arrives to you safe and sound.Happy Bidding! Specs below: Alder body Maple bolt-on neck Rosewood fretboard with 24 jumbo frets Licensed floyd rose bridge HSH configurationReverse Headstock Dot inlays One volume pot, one tone pot and a five way switch
Title: Jackson 1996, PS4, Made in Japan, Performer Series guitar, w/ Seymour Duncan
ConditionDescription: Cosmetically, it is a players guitar. In the right light and angle you can see a 8 inch long finish scratch, and the guitar also has some bumps and dings. Structurally it is in nice condition with a nice straight neck, frets are in nice shape and all the electronics work as they should. If you don't mind a guitar that looks like it has been played, i guess you could call it naturally reliced, but is structurally sound, plays and sounds great too... This might just be the guitar for you.
